<head>YAWN</head><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">打呵欠</item></list>
<div type="definition">
<p>BREATHE out INTENSELY AND INVOLUNTARILY, OFTEN:typically BECAUSE one is TIRED.</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006</p></div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>打呵欠 is the current modern word for yawning.</p>
<p>打哈欠 is a variant of the above.</p>
<p>欠伸 focusses on the stretching of the body which typically accompanies yawning.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p></div></div>
